      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>Neil, H Landman received his Ph.D. from Yale University in 1982 ("Ontogeny and Evolution of Late Cretaceous (Turonian-Santonian) Scaphites") as a student of Karl Waage. Curator of Paleontology at AMNH and curatorial associate at the Yale Peabody Museum.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>Includes photocopies of his 1977 and 1980 field notebooks, as well as some miscellaneous locality information, and photographs and drawings of specimens.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
